    // Parse grammatical structures
    // Check complexity against CEFR descriptors
    // Flag advanced structures in lower levels
  }
}
```

### 3. Consistency Review
- Standardize formatting across all content
- Ensure consistent difficulty progression
- Verify cultural inclusivity
- Check for accessibility compliance

### 4. Platform Integration
```javascript
// Content Management System
class ContentManagementSystem {
  constructor() {
    this.contentDatabase = new Database();
    this.versionControl = new VersionControl();
    this.publishingQueue = new PublishingQueue();
  }

  importContent(source, format) {
    switch(format) {
      case 'markdown':
        return this.parseMarkdown(source);
      case 'json':
        return this.parseJSON(source);
      case 'docx':
        return this.parseDocx(source);
      default:
        throw new Error('Unsupported format');
    }
  }

  formatForPlatform(content) {
    return {
      title: content.title,
      slug: this.generateSlug(content.title),
      category: content.category,
      level: content.cefrLevel,
      fullText: this.processText(content.text),
      difficultWords: this.extractVocabulary(content.text),
      exercises: this.formatExercises(content.exercises),
      assessment: this.formatAssessment(content.assessment)
    };
  }
}
```

### 5. Testing and Feedback
- Deploy to staging environment
- Conduct user testing with target learners
- Gather feedback from educators
- Analyze learning outcome data

### 6. Iteration and Improvement
- Implement feedback-based improvements
- A/B test different content versions
- Monitor engagement metrics
- Continuously update based on learning analytics

## Integration Best Practices

### Export/Import Workflow
```javascript
// Content Pipeline
class ContentPipeline {
  async processContent(rawContent) {
    // 1. Parse and validate
    const parsed = await this.parseContent(rawContent);

    // 2. Apply CEFR standards
    const standardized = await this.applyStandards(parsed);

    // 3. Generate interactive elements
    const interactive = await this.addInteractivity(standardized);

    // 4. Format for platform
    const formatted = await this.formatForPlatform(interactive);

    // 5. Quality check
    const validated = await this.validateQuality(formatted);

    return validated;
  }
}
```

### Naming Conventions
- **Levels**: A1, A2, B1, B2, C1, C2
- **Skills**: reading, writing, listening, speaking
- **Topics**: Use descriptive kebab-case (e.g., 'environmental-awareness')
- **Content Types**: dialogue, story, article, discussion, analysis

### Content Library Organization
```
content/
├── levels/
│   ├── a1/
│   │   ├── dialogues/
│   │   ├── vocabulary/
│   │   └── exercises/
│   ├── a2/
│   ├── b1/
│   ├── b2/
│   ├── c1/
│   └── c2/
├── skills/
│   ├── reading/
│   ├── writing/
│   ├── listening/
│   └── speaking/
└── assessments/
    ├── placement/
    ├── progress/
    └── final/
```

This systematic approach ensures consistent, high-quality content that effectively supports English language learning across all CEFR levels while providing educators and developers with the tools needed to create engaging, interactive learning experiences.

